  "title": "Kitchen Crew",
  "description": "<p>To apply or find out more, please contact<strong> Leong Jia Wei </strong>(Reg No: R25157456) on </p><p>WhatsApp <strong>+65 80358497</strong> or</p><p>email <a href=\"mailto:jiawei@placement.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">jiawei@placement.com.sg</a></p><p><br />\n<strong># Overview #</strong></p><p>My client is an international chain selling Indonesian cuisine with various ingredients such as meat, soup, rice,\nnoodles and vegetables.</p><p>Hiring for new Kitchen Staff/Service crew to support expansion plans at various outlets.<br /></p><p><strong># Key Responsibilities #</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Prepare dishes according\n     to instructions and standardized recipes </strong></li><li><strong>Operate the POS system</strong>, handle cash, and manage digital payments.</li><li><strong>Maintain stall cleanliness</strong>,\n     including wiping counters, washing equipment, clearing trash, and keeping\n     the workspace organised.</li><li><strong>Restock ingredients</strong></li><li><strong>Follow food safety and hygiene guidelines</strong> (SFA\n     requirements, handwashing, glove use, proper storage).</li><li><strong>Manage customer orders</strong> quickly and\n     accurately, especially during peak periods.</li><li><strong>Assist with opening and closing duties</strong> —\n     prepping ingredients, turning on/off machines, counting stock, and closing\n     reports.</li><li>Other forms of<strong> basic customer service</strong>, including addressing complaints or special requests.</li></ul><p><strong># Requirements #</strong></p><ul><li>Former experience in\n     Food & Beverage will be an advantage</li><li>Able to stand for long hours and handle fast-paced environments.</li><li>Able to work <strong>weekends, evenings, shifts and Public Holidays (PH)</strong> as needed.</li><li>Salary scales up based on skills and experience</li><li>Singapore Citizens (SG) and Permanent Residents (PR) preferred.</li></ul>",
